====Group D====
{{main|2006 FIFA World Cup Group D}}
[[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] coasted through in Group D, picking up the maximum number of points, with [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] qualifying in second. [[Iran national football team|Iran]] missed chances against Mexico in their opening 1–3 defeat and were eliminated in their match against Portugal. They fought hard against the Portuguese, but went down 2–0. Their last game against [[Angola national football team|Angola]] ended in 1–1 draw. The Africans had a respectable first World Cup tournament after earning draws with Mexico (0–0) and Iran.

