====Group H====
{{main|2006 FIFA World Cup Group H}}
[[Spain national football team|Spain]] dominated Group H, picking up the maximum number of points, scoring 8 goals, and conceding only 1. [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]], despite being beaten 4–0 by Spain in their first World Cup game, took advantage of the weaker opponents to beat [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] 4–0 and scrape past [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]] 1–0 thanks to a 70th-minute penalty by [[Andriy Shevchenko]], to reach the Round of 16. Saudi Arabia and Tunisia went out of the tournament having 1&nbsp;point each, thanks to a 2–2 draw against each other.

