{{Infobox language family |name=Tebu |altname=Tubu |ethnicity=[[Tubu people]] |region=[[Chad]], [[Libya]], [[Niger]] |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Saharan languages|Saharan]] |fam3=Western Saharan |child1=[[Teda language|Teda]] |child2=[[Daza language|Daza]] |glotto=tebu1238 |glottorefname=Tebu |map=Toubou map.svg }} '''Tebu''' is a small family of two [[Saharan languages]], consisting of [[Daza language|Daza]] and [[Teda language|Teda]]. It is spoken by the two groups of [[Toubou people]], the ''Daza'' and ''Teda''.
Tebu is predominantly spoken in [[Chad]] and in southern [[Libya]] by around 580,000 people. [[Daza language|Daza]] and [[Teda language|Teda]] have an estimated 537,000 and 42,500 speakers, respectively.<ref>[[SIL Ethnologue]] estimates ([http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=dzg Dazaga], [http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=tuq Tedaga]).</ref>
